title: What are the 72 names of the Schemanforasch and their meanings according to the value of their roots?
first_phrase: This text is a list of 72 names of angels categorized by their respective areas of influence. The names are listed in reverse order according to their roots and meanings. The last 200 tokens contain the names from the principalities to the end, along with their corresponding meanings. These names can be useful to those seeking to understand the spiritual realm and its inhabitants.

last_phrase: By examining the roots of the names in the Scheemianforash of the Jews and the method used to form them, one can unlock the key to their meanings and values. However, understanding this subjective interruption of typical realization is essential, and it must not be manipulated objectively. This understanding is vital in the theory and practice of evocation, which we will explore further in the future.
